Text.val: Where clause --> Use of auto recover selection!
The sorting is done by FactoryName to be able to check only once per factoryname.
Checking if the connection to the dispatcher is possible using the factoryname :
No check can be done upfront so initialize with TRUE to prevent invalid logging :
Not recovering because no connection to the Dispatcher could be made.
No Factoryname in Failed messages then check if an error already occured. If so, depending on the severity
of the error a reconnect can or can't be done.
If the ERROR_ID is null, it has not been determined wheter or not the message can be send, so it has to be send to check.
If the reply is succesfully send the 'failed message' record will be deleted by the foreign key constraint (JFM_TAMD_ID).
If the resend reveals that there is no connection to the dispatcher possible (errorId = 40001) then stop
If no resend has been done then return the current Id :
Als er een locked row is, deze negeren en doorgaan naar het volgende record of de taak sluiten. Een andere taak is dan al bezig.
